162
00:11:44,284 --> 00:11:47,720
-So are you in TV too?
-No.

163
00:11:47,921 --> 00:11:49,752
No. l'm a rabbi.

164
00:11:50,557 --> 00:11:53,424
You don't wear an outfit or anything?

165
00:11:53,993 --> 00:11:56,985
Public television wants to do
a documentary...

166
00:11:57,197 --> 00:11:59,495
...on the way l talk and think--

167
00:11:59,699 --> 00:12:02,896
lt's part of their
Creative Mind series.

168
00:12:03,102 --> 00:12:05,400
So l told them about you.

169
00:12:05,605 --> 00:12:08,267
Thanks. l'm working on my own thing.

170
00:12:08,474 --> 00:12:10,499
-A little film.
-Wendy told me.

171
00:12:10,710 --> 00:12:15,238
A film about some philosophy
professor, which is admirable.

172
00:12:15,448 --> 00:12:20,078
But this is a chance to earn
decent money, reach a big audience.

173
00:12:20,286 --> 00:12:23,380
Last thing you need
is me as your biographer.

174
00:12:23,590 --> 00:12:27,959
l make these little films on
toxic waste and starving children.

175
00:12:28,161 --> 00:12:32,757
l'll be frank. You're not my
first choice. lt's a favor to Wendy.

176
00:12:32,966 --> 00:12:37,733
-You never work. She's embarrassed.
-l've worked, but nobody pays me.

177
00:12:37,937 --> 00:12:40,462
l know you don't respect what l do.

178
00:12:40,673 --> 00:12:43,107
But l got a closet full of Emmys.

179
00:12:43,309 --> 00:12:46,506
You think that's bullshit.
Fine. l understand.

180
00:12:46,713 --> 00:12:50,205
Maybe l could use the money
to finish my movie.

181
00:12:50,416 --> 00:12:52,111
l do have some debts.

182
00:12:52,318 --> 00:12:53,683
ldea for farce:

183
00:12:53,886 --> 00:12:58,220
A poor loser agrees to do
the story of a great man's life.

184
00:12:58,424 --> 00:13:01,359
And in the process,
he learns deep values.

185
00:13:04,597 --> 00:13:08,533
-What takes you to Boston?
-I'm lecturing at a symposium,

186
00:13:08,735 --> 00:13:11,135
lncidentally, my name's Dolores.

187
00:13:11,337 --> 00:13:13,032
-Hello, Dolores.
-Hello.

188
00:13:13,239 --> 00:13:15,332
-Pretty name.
-Thank you.

189
00:13:15,975 --> 00:13:19,342
-Do you go to Boston often?
-Not very often,

190
00:13:19,545 --> 00:13:22,343
I don't know anyone
in Boston, actually,

191
00:13:22,548 --> 00:13:23,981
-Really?
-Yeah,

192
00:13:32,358 --> 00:13:33,347
-Morning.
-Hi.

193
00:13:33,559 --> 00:13:36,528
A Miss Paley called,
said it was urgent.

194
00:13:42,669 --> 00:13:46,537
Why did you phone me?
l told you l'd call you.

195
00:13:46,739 --> 00:13:50,766
l couldn't help it.
l was going out of my skin.

196
00:13:52,712 --> 00:13:54,680
l have to see you later.

197
00:13:55,081 --> 00:13:56,605
l have to!

198
00:13:58,051 --> 00:13:59,177
Okay.

199
00:14:00,186 --> 00:14:02,086
After work is okay.

200
00:14:05,358 --> 00:14:06,552
l see it.

201
00:14:07,760 --> 00:14:08,749
Yeah.

202
00:14:09,762 --> 00:14:11,024
l see it.

203
00:14:12,465 --> 00:14:14,399
Oh, God.

204
00:14:15,168 --> 00:14:16,328
What?

205
00:14:17,804 --> 00:14:19,704
l need to take a minute.

206
00:14:22,108 --> 00:14:23,575
What's wrong, Judah?

207
00:14:25,111 --> 00:14:27,204
l'm in such trouble, Ben.

208
00:14:27,480 --> 00:14:28,811
What is it?

209
00:14:29,882 --> 00:14:32,009
l need to talk to someone.

210
00:14:32,552 --> 00:14:33,678
Sure.

211
00:14:35,054 --> 00:14:38,956
l've known you for years.
You're religious. l'm not.

212
00:14:39,158 --> 00:14:42,958
We've differed on many points,
but l do respect you.

213
00:14:43,730 --> 00:14:46,665
-May l confide in you?
-Of course.

214
00:14:47,500 --> 00:14:50,094
Go ahead. Everything's confidential.

215
00:14:54,407 --> 00:14:56,637
l've done a foolish thing.

216
00:14:56,843 --> 00:14:58,640
Senseless. Vain.

217
00:14:58,845 --> 00:15:00,039
Dumb.

218
00:15:03,549 --> 00:15:05,107
Another woman.

219
00:15:09,522 --> 00:15:13,925
Maybe l was flattered, vulnerable.

220
00:15:14,127 --> 00:15:16,857
Maybe because she was
helpless and alone.

221
00:15:17,063 --> 00:15:19,964
But now my life's
about to go up in smoke.

222
00:15:20,466 --> 00:15:24,027
-Can't you break it off?
-The woman won't allow it.

223
00:15:24,537 --> 00:15:27,370
She's young. She's very unstable.

224
00:15:27,573 --> 00:15:29,097
She's an hysteric.

225
00:15:29,475 --> 00:15:31,033
And vindictive.

226
00:15:31,277 --> 00:15:32,835
And it's my fault.

227
00:15:33,045 --> 00:15:36,105
l instigated it. l prolonged it.

228
00:15:36,315 --> 00:15:39,409
l tried to back off,
but l was too weak.

229
00:15:39,619 --> 00:15:42,213
But l promised her nothing.

230
00:15:42,422 --> 00:15:45,220
But did l? l don't even know anymore.

231
00:15:45,425 --> 00:15:48,417
ln the heat of passion,
you say things.

232
00:15:48,628 --> 00:15:51,825
After two years of living
this double life...

233
00:15:52,031 --> 00:15:54,295
...l awakened as if from a dream...

234
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:58,300
-...and realized what l'd be losing.
-lt's called wisdom.

235
00:15:58,504 --> 00:16:00,631
lt comes to some suddenly.

236
00:16:00,840 --> 00:16:04,833
We realize the difference between
what's deep and lasting...

237
00:16:05,044 --> 00:16:08,377
...versus the superficial
payoff of the moment.

238
00:16:08,581 --> 00:16:12,881
l kidded myself about loving her,
but deep down l knew.

239
00:16:13,085 --> 00:16:15,212
Knowing l behaved selfishly...

240
00:16:15,421 --> 00:16:17,981
...for pleasure,
for adventure, for lust.

241
00:16:18,191 --> 00:16:20,853
Sometimes, when there's real love...

242
00:16:21,060 --> 00:16:24,154
