God will punish you?

954
01:10:39,842 --> 01:10:42,811
-Not me. He punishes the wicked.
-Like Hitler?

955
01:10:43,012 --> 01:10:44,479
We're having a Seder!

956
01:10:44,680 --> 01:10:47,808
Six million Jews killed,
they got away with it.

957
01:10:48,017 --> 01:10:51,077
-How'd they get away with it?
-Open your eyes!

958
01:10:51,287 --> 01:10:54,313
Six million Jews.
They got off with nothing.

959
01:10:54,524 --> 01:10:57,891
-How could men do such a thing?
-Might makes right.

960
01:10:58,094 --> 01:11:02,360
-Until the Americans--
-l don't like this talk at Seder.

961
01:11:02,565 --> 01:11:03,827
Okay! All right!

962
01:11:04,033 --> 01:11:07,594
-I think this is interesting,
-Yeah, you do,

963
01:11:07,804 --> 01:11:09,601
There's this joke,

964
01:11:09,806 --> 01:11:11,967
A prizefighter enters the ring.

965
01:11:12,175 --> 01:11:15,633
His brother asks the family priest
to pray for him.

966
01:11:15,845 --> 01:11:19,281
He said, ''Okay.
But if he can punch, it'll help.''

967
01:11:19,482 --> 01:11:23,885
So you're saying you challenge
the moral structure of everything?

968
01:11:24,087 --> 01:11:28,148
Moral structure? You use
that nonsense on your pupils?

969
01:11:28,357 --> 01:11:31,588
You don't find human impulses
basically decent?

970
01:11:31,794 --> 01:11:36,356
-There's basically nothing.
-A cynic, a nihilist. Back to Russia.

971
01:11:36,566 --> 01:11:39,933
Well, listen. l happen
to agree with May...

972
01:11:40,136 --> 01:11:42,195
...when it comes to mumbo jumbo.

973
01:11:42,405 --> 01:11:46,136
But you come to every Seder.
You pray in Hebrew.

974
01:11:46,342 --> 01:11:50,278
l go through the motions.
Like any ritual, it's a habit.

975
01:11:50,480 --> 01:11:54,541
So you say there's no morality
anywhere in the whole world?

976
01:11:54,750 --> 01:11:59,210
For those who want it, it's there.
Nothing's handed down in stone.

977
01:11:59,422 --> 01:12:01,515
Sol's kind of faith is a gift.

978
01:12:01,724 --> 01:12:04,852
lt's like an ear for music
or talent to draw.

979
01:12:05,061 --> 01:12:08,724
You use logic on him all day
and he still believes.

980
01:12:08,931 --> 01:12:12,924
-Must everything be logical?
-And if a man commits a crime?

981
01:12:13,136 --> 01:12:14,694
lf he--

982
01:12:14,904 --> 01:12:16,337
lf he kills?

983
01:12:17,473 --> 01:12:21,136
-ln some way, he'll be punished.
-lf he's caught, Sol.

984
01:12:21,344 --> 01:12:25,940
''What originates from a black deed
will blossom in a foul manner.''

985
01:12:26,149 --> 01:12:29,277
You're relying too heavily
on the Bible.

986
01:12:29,485 --> 01:12:33,922
Whether it's the Old Testament
or Shakespeare, murder will out.

987
01:12:34,123 --> 01:12:37,650
-Who said anything about murder?
-You did.

988
01:12:40,096 --> 01:12:41,427
Did l?

989
01:12:43,666 --> 01:12:46,601
l say, if he can do it
and get away with it...

990
01:12:46,802 --> 01:12:50,704
...and chooses not to be bothered
by ethics, he's home free.

991
01:12:50,907 --> 01:12:53,637
History is written by the winners.

992
01:12:53,843 --> 01:12:57,574
Had the Nazis won,
future generations would understand...

993
01:12:57,780 --> 01:12:59,941
...World War ll quite differently.

994
01:13:00,149 --> 01:13:04,017
Your aunt is brilliant,
but she's had an unhappy life.

995
01:13:04,220 --> 01:13:09,419
And if all your faith is wrong--
l mean, just what if? lf?

996
01:13:09,625 --> 01:13:12,753
l'll still have a better life
than doubters.

997
01:13:12,962 --> 01:13:16,955
Wait a minute. Are you saying
you prefer God to the truth?

998
01:13:17,166 --> 01:13:22,001
-l'll always choose God over truth.
-l agree with him.

999
01:13:22,638 --> 01:13:25,505
l say, what goes around comes around.

1000
01:13:30,613 --> 01:13:35,016
-You okay? l was worried. lt's late.
-l had some business.

1001
01:13:35,218 --> 01:13:36,708
Mrs. Ames is waiting.

1002
01:13:36,919 --> 01:13:39,251
-Any messages?
-You got an odd one.

1003
01:13:39,455 --> 01:13:42,720
A Detective O'Donnell
wanted to talk to you.

1004
01:13:42,925 --> 01:13:47,487
l tried to ask him what about,
but he only wants to talk with you.

1005
01:14:07,316 --> 01:14:10,945
-lt's not a great movie, but it's fun.
-l liked it.

1006
01:14:11,153 --> 01:14:13,485
Maybe l want to be an actress.

1007
01:14:13,689 --> 01:14:18,592
l don't want you to be an actress.
Be on the Supreme Court or a doctor.

1008
01:14:18,794 --> 01:14:20,921
Show business is dog-eat-dog.

1009
01:14:21,130 --> 01:14:26,067
lt's worse than dog-eat-dog. lt's
dog-doesn't-return-other-dog's-calls.

1010
01:14:26,269 --> 01:14:28,294
l should check my service.

1011
01:14:28,504 --> 01:14:31,302
l don't know why.
l never have messages.

1012
01:14:31,507 --> 01:14:35,034
-l call, l hear the girls giggling.
-How's Halley?

1013
01:14:35,244 --> 01:14:38,042
She's great. l'm gonna make my move.

1014
01:14:38,247 --> 01:14:42,343
But l have this ethical dilemma
because l'm married.

1015
01:14:42,551 --> 01:14:45,520
Clifford Stern. Any messages?
Can you check?

1016
01:14:45,721 --> 01:14:48,656
My heart says one thing.
My head, another.

1017
01:14:48,858 --> 01:14:52,589
lt's hard to get your heart
and head together in life.

1018
01:14:52,795 --> 01:14:55,764
ln my case, they're not
even friendly. Yes?

1019
01:14:59,635 --> 01:15:01,068
Really?

1020
01:15:06,709 --> 01:15:08,142
No.

1021
01:15:10,680 --> 01:15:12,204
Okay. Thank you.

1022
01:15:15,751 --> 01:15:17,082
What's wrong?

1023
01:15:20,389 --> 01:15:22,323
Professor Levy...

1024
01:15:22,658 --> 01:15:24,785
...committed suicide.

1025
01:15:26,028 --> 01:15:28,326
But we must always remember,,,

1026
01:15:28,531 --> 01:15:32,126
,,, that we--
When we are born,,,

1027
01:15:32,335 --> 01:15:34,963
,,,we need a great deal of love,,,

1028
01:15:35,171 --> 01:15:38,766
,,,in order to persuade us
to stay in life,

1029
01:15:38,974 --> 01:15:42,774
Once we get that love,
it usually lasts us,

1030
01:15:42,978 --> 01:15:45,606
But the universe is a cold place,

1031
01:15:45,815 --> 01:15:49,273
It's we who invest it
with our feelings,

1032
01:15:49,485 --> 01:15:52,147
And under certain conditions,,,

1033
01:15:52,355 --> 01:15:55,950
,,,we feel that the thing
isn't worth it anymore,

1034
01:15:56,158 --> 01:16:00,720
l came as soon as l heard. l thought
you wouldn't want to be alone.

1035
01:16:00,930 --> 01:16:05,390
God, it's been terrible. l called--
The guy was not sick at all.

1036
01:16:05,601 --> 01:16:09,264
He left a note that said,
''l've gone out the window.''

1037
01:16:09,472 --> 01:16:13,738
A major intellectual, and this
is his note. What does it mean?

1038
01:16:13,943 --> 01:16:15,410
He was a role model.

1039
01:16:15,611 --> 01:16:20,571
-You'd think he'd leave a decent note.
-Did he have family or anything?

1040
01:16:20,783 --> 01:16:25,652
They were killed in the war. lt's
strange. He's seen the worst in life.

1041
01:16:25,855 --> 01:16:30,019
He always said yes to life.
Now today he said no.

1042
01:16:30,226 --> 01:16:33,855
lmagine his students,
how shattered they will be.

1043
01:16:34,063 --> 01:16:38,022
Where l grew up, in Brooklyn,
nobody committed suicide.

1044
01:16:38,234 --> 01:16:42,534
-Everyone was too unhappy.
-This will put a damper on the show.

1045
01:16:42,738 --> 01:16:45,730
l got 600,000 feet of film
on this guy...

1046
01:16:45,941 --> 01:16:48,535
...and he's telling how great life is.

1047
01:16:48,744 --> 01:16:51,474
l'll cut it up,
use it for guitar picks.

1048
01:16:51,680 --> 01:16:54,615
l was thinking,
no matter how elaborate...

1049
01:16:54,817 --> 01:16:57,581
...a philosophical system
you work out...

1050
01:16:57,787 --> 01:17:01,188
...in the end,
it's gotta be incomplete.

1051
01:17:01,390 --> 01:17:05,486
l've been so annoyed all day.
l'm sorry for seeming cranky.

1052
01:17:05,694 --> 01:17:10,188
No, l understand. l just thought
you might want some company.

1053
01:17:13,235 --> 01:17:15,135
No. Don't do that.

1054
01:17:15,704 --> 01:17:18,639
lt's something l've wanted
to do for weeks.

1055
01:17:18,841 --> 01:17:20,900
-You must know.
-You're married.

1056
01:17:21,110 --> 01:17:22,407
Yes, l'm married.

1057
01:17:22,611 --> 01:17:25,944
But, you know, that's
not gonna last. l mean....

1058
01:17:26,148 --> 01:17:27,513
Well, you know...

1059
01:17:27,716 --> 01:17:29,911
...l'm not ready.

1060
01:17:31,654 --> 01:17:34,487
ls there something you're
not telling me?

1061
01:17:34,690 --> 01:17:35,679
No.

1062
01:17:35,891 --> 01:17:38,951
ls there someone else?
Don't say it's Lester.

1063
01:17:39,161 --> 01:17:41,356
lt's me. lt's just me.

1064
01:17:41,564 --> 01:17:45,523
l guess l haven't gotten over
my divorce yet, you know?

1065
01:17:45,734 --> 01:17:49,329
And also, l feel unsettled
about my career.

1066
01:17:49,538 --> 01:17:51,563
l'm very ambitious.

1067
01:17:51,774 --> 01:17:55,505
And that's an area that
l'd like to get consolidated.

1068
01:17:55,711 --> 01:17:58,475
l just feel, you know, unsettled.

1069
01:18:12,795 --> 01:18:14,160
Don't confuse me.

1070
01:18:14,363 --> 01:18:18,629
-l'm not trying to confuse you.
-l don't know what l'm doing.

1071
01:18:19,034 --> 01:18:22,197
l better go. l should just leave.

1072
01:18:22,404 --> 01:18:25,168
-You just got here.
-l know, but l--

1073
01:18:25,541 --> 01:18:29,944
-l'm sorry, l didn't mean--
-No, that's okay. l'll see you soon.

1074
01:18:30,145 --> 01:18:32,477
l'll just-- l'll be seeing you.

1075
01:18:36,318 --> 01:18:37,785
Please come in.

1076
01:18:39,455 --> 01:18:41,582
We read about it in the paper.

1077
01:18:41,790 --> 01:18:46,193
lt's a terrible thing.
She'd been coming here for years.

1078
01:18:46,395 --> 01:18:48,363
-Please, sit down.
-Thank you.

1079
01:18:49,164 --> 01:18:53,498
Just a few questions, doctor.
Records show she phoned you here...

1080
01:18:53,702 --> 01:18:56,569
...and at your home a number of times.

1081
01:18:56,772 --> 01:19:00,572
-She worried about her eyes.
-What was she suffering from?

1082
01:19:00,776 --> 01:19:05,804
Nothing serious. She had
light flashes, and they alarmed her.

1083
01:19:06,015 --> 01:19:08,449
l never found anything very wrong.

1084
01:19:08,651 --> 01:19:11,620
l told her it was just
a common occurrence.

1085
01:19:11,820 --> 01:19:15,620
-She was a hypochondriac?
-No. l wouldn't say that.

1086
01:19:15,824 --> 01:19:17,485
But she was concerned.

1087
01:19:18,160 --> 01:19:21,823
There's nothing she said
you think might be relevant?

1088
01:19:22,031 --> 01:19:23,828
Personal life? Friends?

1089
01:19:24,033 --> 01:19:26,001
No, not really.

1090
01:19:26,869 --> 01:19:28,769
How did she come to you?

1091
01:19:30,339 --> 01:19:34,002
l honestly can't remember.
Possibly another patient.

1092
01:19:34,209 --> 01:19:35,642
Can l get that name?

1093
01:19:35,844 --> 01:19:39,302
lt was a while ago,
and l treat so many patients.

1094
01:19:39,515 --> 01:19:42,348
-Might it be in your records?
-No.

1095
01:19:42,551 --> 01:19:45,543
No. l doubt it very much.

1096
01:19:46,455 --> 01:19:49,185
-Sorry to take up your time.
-That's okay.

1097
01:19:49,391 --> 01:19:52,292
lf you remember anything
that might help...

1098
01:19:52,494 --> 01:19:54,325
-...will you call me?
-Sure.

1099
01:19:54,530 --> 01:19:56,464
-Thank you.
-Pleasure.

1100
01:20:06,508 --> 01:20:08,305
You're having a breakdown!

1101
01:20:08,510 --> 01:20:12,071
They know she phoned me.
l lied. They saw through it.

1102
01:20:12,281 --> 01:20:15,682
-l can't take this.
-Pull yourself together.

1103
01:20:15,884 --> 01:20:19,012
l did it. lt's irrevocable,
and l'm gonna pay.

1104
01:20:19,221 --> 01:20:22,987
l had to fight an urge
to come clean to the police.

1105
01:20:23,192 --> 01:20:27,686
l'm in this with you. l helped you.
l don't wanna go to jail.

1106
01:20:27,896 --> 01:20:32,629
You get ideas about confessing,
and you'll drag me down with you.

1107
01:20:32,835 --> 01:20:34,803
But l won't let that happen.

1108
01:20:35,004 --> 01:20:38,371
-ls that a threat?
-Be a man. You're in the clear.

1109
01:20:38,574 --> 01:20:40,735
-You'll have me killed?
-Nonsense.

1110
01:20:40,943 --> 01:20:43,776
What did you mean by that remark?

1111
01:20:43,979 --> 01:20:46,573
You've helped me in the past. Fine.

1112
01:20:46,782 --> 01:20:48,807
l did you a favor. All right?

1113
01:20:49,018 --> 01:20:53,318
The time to confess was to Miriam
about your mistress.

1114
01:20:53,522 --> 01:20:55,854
Not about this! This is murder.

1115
01:20:56,058 --> 01:21:00,392
You paid for it, l engineered it.
lt's over! Forget about it!

1116
01:21:00,896 --> 01:21:04,457
-One sin leads to a deeper sin.
-You sound like Papa.

1117
01:21:04,667 --> 01:21:08,068
Adultery, fornication, lies, killing.

1118
01:21:08,270 --> 01:21:11,364
-Can you shut up?
-Or what? You'll shut me up?

1119
01:21:11,573 --> 01:21:14,633
One phone call,
like pushing a button right?

1120
01:21:51,191 --> 01:21:54,752
l don't know what's wrong
with you these days.

1121
01:21:55,862 --> 01:21:58,023
l believe in God, Miriam.

1122
01:21:58,898 --> 01:22:03,733
l know it. Because without God,
the world is a cesspool.

1123
01:22:03,937 --> 01:22:07,100
You drink every day.
You never used to.

1124
01:22:07,307 --> 01:22:08,865
lt's something new.

1125
01:22:09,075 --> 01:22:11,543
-God, it's hot.
-Maybe we should go--

1126
01:22:11,745 --> 01:22:15,579
-Don't tell me what to do, damn it!
-Will you calm down?

1127
01:22:18,451 --> 01:22:21,352
l don't feel well.
l'm gonna get some air.

1128
01:22:21,554 --> 01:22:23,283
No, you stay here.

1129
01:22:46,780 --> 01:22:50,272
This homeless story is too long,
I want five pages,

1130
01:22:50,483 --> 01:22:52,212
Five real pages,

1131
01:22:52,419 --> 01:22:56,446
His secretary types it tighter,
He doesn't take a thing out,

1132
01:22:56,656 --> 01:22:58,556
I want Johanson off the show,

1133
01:22:58,758 --> 01:23:02,854
He has cancer, Send him flowers,
He's not funny,

1134
01:23:03,063 --> 01:23:04,257
I want him off,

1135
01:23:04,464 --> 01:23:09,527
Can't anyone write funny anymore? I'm
supposed to write everything myself?

1136
01:23:09,736 --> 01:23:12,227
Write, direct and produce it myself?

1137
01:23:12,439 --> 01:23:16,671
I can't believe this!
Look at the people out there!

1138
01:23:16,876 --> 01:23:21,540
These people are looking for
something funny in their lives!

1139
01:23:21,748 --> 01:23:24,740
They're waiting for something funny!

1140
01:23:43,303 --> 01:23:45,134
This is terrible.

1141
01:23:45,405 --> 01:23:47,305
What are you doing to me?

1142
01:23:47,507 --> 01:23:50,408
This isn't a profile
of a creative mind!

1143
01:23:50,810 --> 01:23:55,804
It's tough for a woman in this
profession, Men always hit on them,

1144
01:23:56,015 --> 01:23:58,984
What is this? When did you shoot that?

1145
01:23:59,185 --> 01:24:02,643
l was lurking around the corner.
l couldn't resist.

1146
01:24:02,856 --> 01:24:05,324
I don't wanna do it
in a vulgar way,,,

1147
01:24:05,525 --> 01:24:08,289
,,,and take it off
from what I see here,

1148
01:24:08,495 --> 01:24:11,055
I wanna find out what's in here,

1149
01:24:11,264 --> 01:24:14,927
So I gotta spend some time,
have dinner together,

1150
01:24:15,135 --> 01:24:17,228
l'm taking over this film.

1151
01:24:17,437 --> 01:24:21,168
-You can't finish my film.
-l can't? Read your contract.

1152
01:24:21,374 --> 01:24:24,969
-You promised.
-The idea was to show the real me.

1153
01:24:25,178 --> 01:24:28,705
l'm not perfect, but l don't
promote values that--

1154
01:24:28,915 --> 01:24:30,280
Let me quote you:

1155
01:24:30,483 --> 01:24:33,281
''--deaden the sensibilities
of democracy.''

1156
01:24:33,486 --> 01:24:36,011
You're fired. Get out of here!

1157
01:24:36,222 --> 01:24:38,554
Go! Thank you! Goodbye!

1158
01:24:38,892 --> 01:24:43,090
If it bends, it's funny,
If it breaks, it isn't,

1159
01:24:44,030 --> 01:24:47,591
Don't get discouraged.
You have your own vision.

1160
01:24:47,801 --> 01:24:52,170
Why was he so mad? As if nobody
was ever compared to Mussolini.

1161
01:24:52,372 --> 01:24:57,503
l'd no idea you'd cut it like this. l
could've told you they'd never use it.

1162
01:24:57,710 --> 01:25:00,042
They want an upbeat profile.

1163
01:25:00,246 --> 01:25:03,807
He's gonna re-cut it
and make himself into a saint.

1164
01:25:04,017 --> 01:25:08,454
Wendy's right. l'm jealous of him
with his limos and his money.

1165
01:25:08,655 --> 01:25:12,421
-You have your own style.
-Listen. Marry me. l'm serious.

1166
01:25:12,625 --> 01:25:14,820
That's all l want. Marry me.

1167
01:25:15,028 --> 01:25:18,259
l'm crazy about you.
My marriage won't last.

1168
01:25:18,465 --> 01:25:22,265
l gotta talk to you.
Can we sit down for a second?

1169
01:25:22,469 --> 01:25:25,700
l'm not joking.
l'm really nuts about you.

1170
01:25:25,905 --> 01:25:27,805
l'm going away.

1171
01:25:30,043 --> 01:25:32,341
Yeah? Meaning what?

1172
01:25:33,146 --> 01:25:37,674
l've got a chance to produce
a couple of shows in London...

1173
01:25:37,884 --> 01:25:40,478
...and, you know, l couldn't say no.

1174
01:25:41,754 --> 01:25:46,384
-How long are you going for?
-Well, probably three or four months.

1175
01:25:46,926 --> 01:25:49,588
Three or four months?

1176
01:25:50,763 --> 01:25:54,927
Jesus. You're kidding.
What a discouraging thought.

1177
01:25:55,134 --> 01:25:57,227
But l think it's a good thing...

1178
01:25:57,437 --> 01:26:01,874
...because l need-- Well,
it will give me a little distance.

1179
01:26:02,075 --> 01:26:05,909
About 3000 miles, to be exact.
When are you leaving?

1180
01:26:06,112 --> 01:26:08,876
Oh, l guess 1 0 days or so.

1181
01:26:10,183 --> 01:26:11,650
God, l'm--

1182
01:26:16,656 --> 01:26:20,490
God, l'm gonna miss you.
l don't know what to say.

1183
